The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, April 03, 2004 				 Avaya takes full control
 OUR CORRESPONDENTMumbai, April 2: The Tata group will sell its 25.1 per cent stake in Tata Telecom to the US-based Avaya Inc, its joint venture partner.																								The decision is in line with the groups strategy to focus on the telecom services business, while Tata Telecom would build on the business of providing converged communications solutions to enterprises. 
